# TypeScript Core Standards

## Type Safety
- Enable `strict: true` in tsconfig.json
- NEVER use `any` type (use `unknown` as escape hatch)
- All function parameters and returns MUST have explicit types

## Code Style
- Prefer `interface` over `type` for object shapes
- Use `const` objects instead of `enum`
- No default exports except for page components

## Functional Patterns
- Use `readonly` for immutable props
- Prefer `const` assertions (`as const`) for literal types
- Use discriminated unions for state machines